%I A393927 #18 Mar 19 2026 23:05:27
%S A393927 3,7,28,34,35,66,74,84,116,125
%N A393927 Numbers k such that the set {2,3,...,k} is a P-position for the game where players remove a number and all its divisors in turn.
%C A393927 Two players remove a number and all divisors of it in turn from an initial number set containing 2 to m. The player who removes the last number wins the game.
%C A393927 This sequence gives values m so that the first player loses the game; that is, the initial set {2,...,m} forms a P-position of the game.
%e A393927 For number set {2,3,4}, if the first player chooses 4 in first round, both 2 and 4 will be removed so that the other player could choose the last number 3 to win the game. To win the game, the first player will choose number 2 and left set {3,4} to win the game. So that 4 is not in the sequence.
%e A393927 For number set {2,3}, either the first player chooses 2 or 3, the other player could pick the other number to win the game, so the first player always loses the game and a(1)=3.
%Y A393927 Cf. A053398, A019312.
%K A393927 nonn,more
